### 4b. Coaching Brief (coach-facing)

This is for your eyes. Be direct. Name what you see.

```
## Coaching Brief — [Team Name]

### Top Patterns
[3 patterns that explain the team's underlying dynamics — not surface observations, but what those observations point to.
Example: "The team has strong technical skills but lacks psychological safety, which is suppressing the improvement cycle."]

### Dimension Deep-Dives
[For each Red and Amber dimension only:]
**[Dimension name]** 🔴/🟡
What's happening: [1–2 sentences]
Why it matters: [1 sentence on downstream impact]
What to explore: [1–2 coaching questions or angles to investigate]

### Recommended Focus Areas
[3–5 prioritized interventions, ordered by leverage — the things where improvement unlocks other improvements.
Format: **[Intervention]** — [Why this, why now, 1–2 sentences]]

### Questions to Bring to the Team
[3–5 coaching questions, specific enough to be useful, open enough to invite real dialogue]
```

---

### 4c. Team-Facing Summary (optional)

Tone: honest, constructive, written in "we" language. Focused on shared growth, not diagnosis.

```
## Team Health Snapshot — [Team Name] — [Date]

### What's going well
[Green dimensions + specific strengths to name and reinforce]

### Where we're growing
[Amber dimensions + framing as growth edges, not failures]

### Where we need to focus together
[Red dimensions + what improvement looks like, not just what's broken]

### Next steps we can own
[2–3 team-owned actions — specific, achievable, tied to the above]
```

