### 4d. Leadership Summary (optional)

Tone: concise, risk-aware, investment-framed. One page.

```
## Team Health Summary — [Team Name] — [Date]
Prepared for: [Role/Audience]

**Overall Health:** [Strong / Developing / At Risk]

### Top Risks Requiring Leadership Attention
1. [Risk] — [Impact if unaddressed]
2. [Risk] — [Impact if unaddressed]

### What the Team Needs from Leadership
[Concrete asks — funding, decisions, air cover, reduced dependencies, etc.]

### Recommended Follow-Up
[Timeframe, what to watch for, suggested next touchpoint]
```

